# Hermes Agent - Cline Rules

## Hermes Run Command
When the user types "hermes run" followed by a task description, execute:

```bash
/Users/_Hermes/hermes-agent/run.sh "task description here"
```

Examples:
- User: `hermes run summarize this file`
  → Run: `/Users/_Hermes/hermes-agent/run.sh "Summarize this file"`

- User: `hermes run review the code in src/`
  → Run: `/Users/_Hermes/hermes-agent/run.sh "Review the code in src/"`

- User: `hermes run --model "anthropic/claude-opus-4.6" --task "deep analysis of auth module"`
  → Run: `/Users/_Hermes/hermes-agent/run.sh --model "anthropic/claude-opus-4.6" --task "deep analysis of auth module"`

## Setup Required
Before running Hermes, ensure:
1. API key is set in `/Users/_Hermes/hermes-agent/.env` — uncomment `OPENROUTER_API_KEY=` and add your key
2. Virtual environment exists at `venv/`
3. Run script is at `run.sh`